RIYADH: Saudi Arabia's Deputy Defense Minister Prince Khalid bin Salman has reviewed the latest Yemen developments with US envoy Tim Lenderking. "I emphasized the commitment of the coalition to support Yemen and apply all measures to reach a political resolution that guarantees security for the region and meet the needs of the brotherly Yemeni people," Prince Khalid said on Twitter.  Reviewed the latest developments in Yemen with U.S Envoy Tim Lenderking. I emphasized the commitment of the coalition to support Yemen and apply all measures to reach a political resolution that guarantees security for the region and meet the needs of the brotherly Yemeni people. pic.twitter.com/tHAhezXBTC — Khalid bin Salman خالد بن سلمان (@kbsalsaud) November 9, 2021